An appellate court ordered the trial of the four officers accused of killing Amadou Diallo to be moved to Albany County, ruling on Thursday that a fair trial would be impossible in the Bronx because of ``the public clamor'' about the case.
Moving the trial to Albany, a predominantly white area, could lessen the respect with which many residents of New York City view the verdict.
The officers were uniformly described as pleased by the news that the trial would go to Albany County.
